I will tell you how to be a person who is not lazy at work:
#1. Set Clear Goals Determine what you want to achieve in your work. Make goals that are specific, measurable, and achievable. This will help you stay focused and motivated. 
# 2. Create an Effective Schedule Make an effective schedule to organize your time and tasks. Prioritize the most important tasks that must be completed first. 
# 3. Start the Day with High Energy Start your day with an energy-boosting activity, such as exercise or meditation. This will help you stay focused and motivated throughout the day.
# 4. Focus on One Task Focus on one task at a time. Don't try to do many tasks at once, as this can make you feel tired and unfocused.
# 5. Get enough rest Make sure you get enough rest. Getting enough sleep and taking regular breaks can help you stay focused and motivated.
# 6. Eliminate Distractions Eliminate distractions that can distract you, such as social media or email. Use apps or tools that can help you stay focused.
# 7. Give Yourself a Gift Reward yourself when you reach a goal or complete a difficult task. This will help you stay motivated and focused. 
# 8. Ask for Help If Needed Don't hesitate to ask for help if you need it. Asking for help from colleagues or mentors can help you stay focused and motivated. 
# 9. Set a Time Limit Set a time limit for completing the task. This will help you stay focused and motivated.
# 10. Evaluate and Improve Evaluation
